# Ready-Go — Project Context

You are helping me refine and perfect a full-stack SaaS product called **Ready-Go**.
This is NOT a new project. The core system is already built and deployed on Vercel.
Your job is to help me clean, refine, fix bugs, and add features to an existing codebase.

Read this entire document before responding to anything.

---

## What Ready-Go is

A portfolio website generator for software engineers. Users sign up, fill in their
content via an admin panel, customize the visual theme, and get a publicly shareable
portfolio website + downloadable PDF resume — all without writing code.

---

## Two surfaces

1. **Admin panel** — protected at `/admin/*`, requires auth
2. **Portfolio website** — public at `/portfolio/[uid]`, no auth required

---

## Tech stack (do not suggest alternatives)

- **Framework**: Next.js 16, App Router, TypeScript strict mode
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui components
- **Database + Auth + Storage**: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Supabase Auth, Supabase Storage)
- **State**: Zustand (theme live-preview store only)
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod (client + server validation on every form)
- **PDF generation**: @react-pdf/renderer (100% client-side, no Puppeteer)
- **Email**: via Supabase authenticated
- **Deployment**: Vercel (free tier)
- **Package manager**: npm
- **AI coding tool**: Google AntiGravity (agent-first IDE)
- **Version control**: GitHub (private repo)

