## Database tables (all in Supabase PostgreSQL)

### One-per-user (unique on user_id)
- `profiles` — id (FK auth.users), username, full_name, email, avatar_url
- `themes` — all theme tokens (colors, fonts, radius, spacing, mode, animation, preset_name)
- `hero` — headline, subheadline, tagline, profile_image_url, cta texts, typing_texts[]
- `about` — bio, location, availability_status, years_of_experience
- `resume_settings` — default_template, include_photo, ats_mode

### Many-per-user (full CRUD)
- `experiences` — company, role, dates, is_current, description, tech_stack[]
- `projects` — title, description, urls, tech_stack[], is_featured
- `skills` — name, category, proficiency (1-5), years_of_experience
- `education` — institution, degree, field_of_study, years, gpa, honors
- `certifications` — name, issuer, dates, credential_url
- `testimonials` — author details, content, linkedin_url
- `blog_posts` — title, excerpt, url, published_at, tags[]
- `awards` — title, issuer, date, description, url
- `open_source_contributions` — repo_name, repo_url, language, stars, role
- `social_links` — platform, url, display_order
- `section_settings` — section_key, is_visible, display_order
- `contact_submissions` — sender_name, sender_email, message, is_read, portfolio_owner_id

### RLS pattern
- All content tables: public SELECT (portfolio visitors can read), owner-only INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
- `resume_settings`: owner-only all operations
- `contact_submissions`: public INSERT, owner-only SELECT/UPDATE/DELETE
- Storage (media bucket): public SELECT, authenticated INSERT, owner DELETE (/{user_id}/ prefix)

### Supabase triggers (fire on auth.users INSERT)
1. `handle_new_user` — creates: profile, theme (Minimal defaults), hero (placeholder), about, resume_settings
2. `handle_new_user_section_settings` — creates 11 section_settings rows (hero/about/experience/projects/skills/education visible; rest hidden)

