## Theme engine (critical — every agent must follow this)

CSS custom properties injected into `:root` on every page:
```
--color-primary, --color-accent, --color-background, --color-surface, --color-text
--font-heading, --font-body
--border-radius, --border-radius-sm
--spacing-unit
--transition-speed, --transition-easing
```

Tailwind classes mapped to these vars:
```
bg-primary, bg-accent, bg-background, bg-surface, text-app-text
font-heading, font-body
rounded-[var(--border-radius)]
p-[var(--spacing-unit)]
transition-all duration-[var(--transition-speed)] ease-[var(--transition-easing)]
```

**Hard rules:**
- NEVER hardcode Tailwind color classes (bg-indigo-600, text-gray-900, bg-white etc.)
- NEVER hardcode rounded-md / rounded-lg on cards, buttons, inputs
- NEVER hardcode font families
- Dark mode via `dark:` prefix + `dark` class toggled on `<html>` by ThemeProvider
- SSR: theme injected via `<style id="ready-go-theme">:root{...}</style>` in layout.tsx
- Client: ThemeProvider (Zustand) keeps style tag in sync for live preview

---

## PDF resume system

- Library: `@react-pdf/renderer` (browser-only, zero server involvement)
- Three templates: ExecutivePDF (two-col), MinimalPDF (mono), CreativePDF (bold header)
- All templates use react-pdf primitives: `<Document>`, `<Page>`, `<View>`, `<Text>`, `<Link>`, `<Image>`
- All styles are inline StyleSheet objects — NO Tailwind inside templates
- Fonts registered via `registerResumeFonts()` in `src/lib/resume-fonts.ts`
- Preview: `BlobProvider` → `<embed>` on desktop, card + open/download buttons on mobile
- Mobile detection: `navigator.userAgent` in `useEffect` (avoids hydration mismatch)
- Public access: visitors go to `/portfolio/[uid]/resume` → `PublicResumeViewer` fetches data client-side

---

## Admin panel responsiveness

- Mobile: slide-in sidebar drawer with hamburger button in sticky top bar
- Desktop: sidebar always visible on left
- Implemented via `AdminShell` client component in `src/components/admin/layout/admin-shell.tsx`
- Sidebar closes automatically on route change (via `usePathname` effect)
- All page content: `max-w-4xl mx-auto` wrapper
- PDF viewer hidden on mobile (replaced with open/download buttons)

---

## Key rules for all code in this project

1. Server components by default — `'use client'` only when interaction requires it
2. All DB access via server actions or API routes — never raw Supabase calls in client components (except public portfolio/resume fetches via anon client)
3. NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY on client, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY only on server
4. All forms: React Hook Form + Zod (validate both client and server)
5. Images via Supabase Storage (/{user_id}/filename) — never binary in DB
6. Use `src/proxy.ts` not `middleware.ts` — Next.js 16 convention, named export `proxy`
7. Never commit .env files — all secrets in .env.local only
8. Never hardcode colors, fonts, or radius — always use theme CSS vars

